{
  "_comment": "ERP master-code correction editor dictionary. Mirrors doc-fields.json's shape. One entry per correctable field, grouped by 'section'. The server (Handle-ErpEditSeed) reads each field's current value from the ERP column named in 'readFrom' (suffix '..5' = join add1..add5 into one block); for a 'code' field it also resolves the code's current master NAME (custsub/linermstr/portmstr/servmstr) and returns it in the seed 'resolved' map so the editor can show 'code -> name'. On save, ONLY changed fields are pushed to Swivel /booking/update, mapped by 'writeKey'. A field with no 'writeKey' is read-only.",
  "_fieldmap_verified": "2026-06-13 on live fm3khkg (HKG pilot): party codes shpr_code/cgne_code/not1_code/agn2_code(delivery agent)/rcustomer(controlling cust)/iliner(liner) are nvarchar(8/10); incoterm = blhead.routing & awbhead.routing (free text, e.g. FOB) with NO master table (incoterm lookup is the fixed Incoterms-2020 list, served by /api-ops/erp-master?kind=incoterm); service = blhead.service/awbhead.service -> servmstr.service/desc1; pol/pod -> portmstr.code/port_ldes1; custsub key = code2 -> doc_e_name; linermstr key = code -> name. Per-party phone = sphone/cphone/nphone/aphone; per-party tax = *_txncode.",
  "_writekeys_confirmed": "ALL write keys verified 2026-06-14 against the Swivel OpenAPI spec (3rd-erpapi.json), NewBooking.bookingParty + top-level. bookingParty keys: shipperPartyCode/Name/Address/ContactPhone/TaxCode, consigneePartyCode/Name/Address/ContactPhone/TaxCode, notifyPartyPartyCode/Name/Address (double 'Party' is the real key), agentPartyCode/Name/Address, linerAgentPartyCode, controllingCustomerPartyCode. Top-level: incoTermsCode, serviceCode, portOfLoadingCode, portOfDischargeCode, bookingContainers[] (containerNo/sealNo/containerTypeCode/quantity; the item also has soNo = liner SO, available for a future round). Carrier/vessel/voyage and dates exist in the schema but are deliberately not editable here.",

